// EI's one-instruction delay window. EI enables IFF1/IFF2 effective AFTER
// the NEXT instruction completes. Pulse INT during the EI's own M1 and the
// following NOP — the model should defer INT acceptance until the NOP
// after EI has finished, observable as: the INTA M-cycle starts AFTER the
// second NOP's M-cycle, not immediately at EI's end.
@0000
ED 56              // IM 1
FB                 // EI         (during this and the next NOP, INT is masked)
00                 // NOP        (this is the EI shadow window)
00                 // NOP        (INT may now be accepted)
C3 03 00           // JP 0x0003  (loop in NOPs)
@0038
76                 // HALT (IM1 vector)
